===Noun===
{{en-noun|~|es|echos}}

# A [[reflect]]ed [[sound]] that is heard again by its initial observer.
#* {{rfdatek|en|Shakespeare}}
#*: The babbling '''echo''' mocks the hounds.
#* {{rfdatek|en|Alexander Pope}}
#*: The woods shall answer, and the '''echo''' ring.
#* {{RQ:Wodehouse Offing|chapter=X|passage=“Then what is your little trouble?” “My little trouble!” I felt that this sort of thing must be stopped at its source. It was only ten minutes to dressing-for-dinner time, and we could go on along these lines for hours. “Listen, old crumpet,” I said patiently. “Make up your mind whether you are my old friend Reginald Herring or an '''echo''' in the Swiss mountains. If you're simply going to repeat every word I say –”}}
#* {{quote-journal|en|year=2013|month=May-June|author=[http://www.americanscientist.org/authors/detail/william-e-conner-1 William E. Conner]| title=[http://www.americanscientist.org/issues/feature/2013/3/an-acoustic-arms-race An Acoustic Arms Race]| volume=101| issue=3| page=206-7| magazine={{w|American Scientist}}| passage=Earless ghost swift moths become “invisible” to echolocating bats by forming mating clusters close (less than half a meter) above vegetation and effectively blending into the clutter of '''echoes''' that the bat receives from the leaves and stems around them.}}
# An [[utterance]] repeating what has just been said.
# {{lb|en|poetry}} A [[device]] in [[verse]] in which a [[line]] ends with a [[word]] which recalls the sound of the last word of the preceding line.
# {{lb|en|figurative}} Sympathetic recognition; response; answer.
#* {{rfdatek|en|Fuller}}
#*: Fame is the '''echo''' of actions, resounding them.
#* {{rfdatek|en|Robert Louis Stevenson}}
#*: Many kind, and sincere speeches found an '''echo''' in his heart.
# {{lb|en|computing}} The displaying on the [[command line]] of the command that has just been executed.
# The letter ''E'' in the [[ICAO spelling alphabet]].
# {{lb|en|whist|bridge}} A [[signal]], played in the same manner as a [[trump]] signal, made by a player who holds four or more trumps (or, as played by some, exactly three trumps) and whose [[partner]] has led trumps or signalled for trumps.
# {{lb|en|whist|bridge}} A signal showing the number held of a plain [[suit]] when a [[high card]] in that suit is led by one's partner.
# {{lb|en|medicine|colloquial}} [[echocardiography|Echocardiography]] or [[echocardiogram]].

